The paper presents a framework for constructing program synthesizers that take natural language inputs and produce expressions in a target DSL. This involves learning optimal weights and classifiers using NLP features. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) techniques, which suggest cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as likely sub-categories. The paper also involves software engineering (SE) aspects, such as constructing synthesizers from DSL definitions and training data, which suggest cs.SE (Software Engineering) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves learning optimal weights and classifiers, which suggest cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible sub-category.
